Salgado Says ECB Trying to Keep Bonds at ‘Reasonable’ Level

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-09-20T07:40:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/salgado-says-ecb-trying-to-keep-bonds-at-reasonable-level.html
Spanish Finance Minister  Elena
Salgado  said the  European Central Bank  is trying to prevent
secondary-market bond prices “falling below what would be
reasonable, taking into account the situation of each country.”
She spoke in an interview on Antena 3 television today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas at 
